channel.title: Help with ip address
channel.description:
OK so when i go to no-ip.com to make my no-ip ip what one do i select?
Host Type: DNS Host (A) DNS Host (Round Robin) DNS Alias (CNAME) Port 80 Redirect Web Redirect
What one??And also i got DUC v2.2.1 how do i use it???And i got a ip address http://68.189.55.125:43594/ how do i use this..And when i go to my source it works but when i go to Mopar server status it says its offline (Help Please)And also people always say do you have a router I'm retarded i dont know what a router is so please help me :confused:(Thank You

item.title: Help with ip address
item.dc:creator: @JBJr JBJr
item.description:
@JBJr wrote:

I chose DNS Host (A) and mine works fine.

DUC v2.2.1 is something that updates your no-ip, I dont really use it much, so you might wanna get some help from someone else for that one :/.

Your parents should know all about your router. If you have one, then then you’ll need to portforward.

Get all of your portforwarding info at www.portforward.com

The ip address 68.189.55.125 is the ip of your computer. Every computer has a different IP address.
